# Server Actions Rules

## Conventions
- All mutations go through Server Actions in `app/actions/`
- Always validate inputs with `zod` at the top of every action
- Always call `requireAdmin()` or `requireJudge()` at the start of protected actions
- Always revalidate affected paths with `revalidatePath()` after mutations
- Return `{ success: true, data }` or `{ success: false, error: string }` — never throw to the client
- Never use API routes for mutations — Server Actions only (except webhooks, UploadThing, and AI routes)

## Pattern
```ts
"use server"

import { z } from "zod"
import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache"
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma"
import { requireAdmin } from "@/lib/auth"

const CreateEventSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  type: z.nativeEnum(EventType),
  judgingMode: z.nativeEnum(JudgingMode),
})

export async function createEvent(input: unknown) {
  const admin = await requireAdmin()
  const data = CreateEventSchema.parse(input)

  const event = await prisma.event.create({ data })
  revalidatePath("/events")
  return { success: true, data: event }
}
```

## Full List of Actions to Implement

### app/actions/events.ts
- `createEvent(input)` — admin only
- `updateEvent(id, input)` — admin only
- `deleteEvent(id)` — admin only
- `cloneEvent(id)` — copy categories, criteria, judge assignments to new event
- `getEvents()` — admin only
- `getEventById(id)`
- `setEventStatus(id, status: EventStatus)`
- `toggleResultsPublic(id, isPublic: boolean)`

### app/actions/projects.ts
- `createProject(input)` — public, no auth (teacher submission)
- `approveProject(id)` — admin only
- `rejectProject(id)` — admin only
- `reassignCategory(id, categoryId)` — admin only
- `getProjectsByEvent(eventId)`
- `getProjectById(id)`
- `deleteProject(id)` — admin only, also deletes UploadThing files

### app/actions/scoring.ts
- `saveScore(assignmentId, items, notes, status)` — judge only
- `resetScore(assignmentId)` — admin only (unlocks a submitted score)
- `getScoreByAssignment(assignmentId)`
- `getLeaderboard(eventId, categoryId?)` — returns projects sorted by avg score
- `flagConflict(assignmentId)` — judge flags conflict of interest, auto-unassigns

### app/actions/categories.ts
- `createCategory(eventId, name, color)` — admin only
- `updateCategory(id, input)` — admin only
- `deleteCategory(id)` — admin only
- `addCriterion(categoryId, input)` — admin only
- `updateCriterion(id, input)` — admin only
- `deleteCriterion(id)` — admin only
- `reorderCriteria(categoryId, orderedIds: string[])` — admin only

### app/actions/judges.ts
- `inviteJudge(email, eventId)` — creates JudgeInvite, sends Resend email
- `acceptInvite(token)` — marks invite as used, links judge to event
- `getJudgesByEvent(eventId)` — admin only
- `assignJudgeToProject(judgeId, projectId)` — admin only
- `removeJudgeFromProject(assignmentId)` — admin only
- `removeJudgeFromEvent(judgeId, eventId)` — admin only
- `getJudgeProgress(judgeId, eventId)` — returns { scored, assigned, percent }

### app/actions/ai.ts
- `generateAbstractSummary(projectId)` — called after project creation
- `generateSchoolFeedback(projectId)` — admin triggers after event closes
- `generateResultsReport(eventId)` — admin only, full narrative export
